{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2ea4a826-9e08-440c-ab78-8031ae1ecb16","content":"Yes, you'll have **compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 requires at minimum **.NET Framework 4.6.2** and **.NET 6.0+** (or .NET Core 3.1 in some earlier v3 releases, but net5.0 and netcoreapp3.1 are out-of-support targets).\n\n**Problems with your current targets:**\n\n| Target | Issue |\n|--------|-------|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported by MSTest v3 |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Not supported — .NET 5 is end-of-life; upgrade to `net6.0` or later |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Not supported — .NET Core 3.1 is end-of-life; upgrade to `net6.0` or later |\n\n**To migrate successfully:**\n\n1. Update `TargetFrameworks` to replace unsupported TFMs (e.g., `net6.0;net462` or `net8.0;net462`).\n2. Replace the two MSTest packages with the unified `MSTest` meta-package (v3+):\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n   ```\n3. Review any breaking API changes (e.g., `DeploymentItem` behavior, removed `Assert` overloads).\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"19f2274c-6d85-48ca-85c2-2e7a49bdf44d","outputTokens":351,"requestId":"0404:F6A9A:16602E6:17D255B:6A033805"},"id":"b616a4e8-6121-42a4-afa6-176c76f3411a","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:24:16.006Z","parentId":"0562ab51-59c6-4c9c-91d8-bb71cec1693a"}
